Text:
Thanks for the upload.

Video quality was good. But the audio for part one was about half a second delayed. Also the video ended before the final whistle. I would guess it was just before the whistle but I don't know.  

Thanks again.

I found that a -350 mSec. audio delay was sufficient to compensate for sound being off cue (ty VLC), and I can't look yet to see whether anything happened after the recording ended and before the game ended (I don't want to see results from other games yet).  I'm assuming not.
